
Compile the file wave.c using:
   icc -Wall -mcmodel=large -O3 -o wave wave.c -lm

The program 'wave' has a couple of command-line options:

  -f <int n>    : compute n frames
  -src <int n>  : simulation with n wave sources
  -bw  <0 or 1> : black-and-white(1) or colour(1) images
  -n <int n>    : number of grid cells (width=height)
  -t <float dt> : time step (in seconds) between two iterations
  -g <float dx> : grid spacing (distance between neighbouring grid cells)
  -s <float v>  : velocity of waves

